+# ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE
+
+Summaries for scanner-reported CVEs where no code patch is required on Ubuntu Jammy `glibc` 2.35.
+
+## CVE-2026-4437 — Not applicable on glibc 2.35 (Ubuntu Jammy)
+
+### Overview
+
+CVE-2026-4437 affects `gethostbyaddr` / `gethostbyaddr_r` when the DNS NSS backend parses PTR responses. The upstream bug is in `getanswer_ptr()`: the answer loop used `while (ancount > 0)` without decrementing `ancount`, so parsing could continue past the answer section into authority/additional records.
+
+**Upstream fix:** commit `9f5f18a` — change to `for (; ancount > 0; --ancount)` ([BZ #34014](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34014)).
+
+### Why Jammy does not need this patch
+
+| Item | Jammy (2.35) | Affected releases (2.37+) |
+|------|--------------|---------------------------|
+| Function | `getanswer_r()` | `getanswer_ptr()` |
+| Answer loop | `while (ancount-- > 0 && ...)` | `while (ancount > 0)` (buggy) |
+| Introduced in | glibc 2.35 base | glibc 2.37 resolver refactor |
+
+Ubuntu Jammy ships glibc **2.35-0ubuntu3.x**. The vulnerable function **`getanswer_ptr()` does not exist** in this tree. The upstream patch hunks fail to apply (missing symbols / wrong line numbers).
+
+Jammy's resolver already decrements the answer count on each iteration, so the section-boundary defect addressed by CVE-2026-4437 is **not present**.
+
+### Verdict
+
+**No code patch required** — not applicable to glibc 2.35. Scanners may still flag this CVE against Jammy packages because NVD lists glibc 2.34–2.43 broadly; the actual vulnerable code path appears only from glibc 2.37.
+
+### References
+
+- [NVD – CVE-2026-4437](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-4437)
+- [Sourceware BZ #34014](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34014)
+- [Upstream fix – 9f5f18a](https://sourceware.org/git/?p=glibc.git;a=commit;h=9f5f18aab40ec6b61fa49a007615e6077e9a979b)
+<!-- SECURITY-RELEASE-ANCHOR -->
