Description: CVE-2026-4046 - Use pending character state in IBM1390, IBM1399 character sets
 The iconv() function crashes due to an assertion failure when converting
 inputs from IBM1390 or IBM1399 character sets.  When the output buffer
 terminates between dual 4-byte UCS-4 sequences during conversion of
 combining characters, a restart triggers the assertion.  This fix uses
 the __count state variable to store the pending character (following the
 example in iso-2022-jp-3.c), avoiding the need to restart the conversion
 and preventing the assertion from being reached.
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/git/?p=glibc.git;a=commit;h=d6f08d1cf027f4eb2ba289a6cc66853722d4badc
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33980
